{"active_answer": "a solid stick like a marlinspike", "active_index": 338, "active_question": "What specific tool is recommended to help untie knots in case they become hard to untie?", "audit_index": 4, "decision": "edit", "document_sha256": "f83771d810b2b197ec3a0fb58660ac529b996951413e58fa87ff48e37f52a6d7", "edited_answer": "a solid stick such as a marlinspike", "edited_question": "What tool does Rope365 suggest for loosening knots that become hard to untie?", "fact_id": "fact-568e19d1c85f56b99ce1", "paraphrase_rationale": "The revised Q&A identifies Rope365, asks directly about the tool’s function, and normalizes the example phrase without changing it.", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 338, "baseline_rows": 536, "baseline_sha256": "c7eec4ce0778e3c1a720a0bcce24560826d28c2031476a54a1c1dee053b63af3", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The revised Q&A identifies Rope365, asks directly about the tool’s function, and normalizes the example phrase without changing it.", "reason_code": "attribute_and_naturalize_marlinspike_guidance", "review_pass": "rope365_incident_prevention_and_response_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v82", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 6, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 1, "question_tokens": 16, "risk_score": 3, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v82", "source": "rope365", "source_document": "data/raw/rope_resources_v1/rope365__7b5d548036392d65fec7.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "52bd91ac138ed002c3c46ccde4233dc586c1f59297e77ff254cefeda6f779018", "source_support": "manual_paraphrase", "support_evidence": "Safety shears and safety hooks are great for cutting rope in case of an emergency. Keeping them directly on you is even safer. Regular knives or kitchen scissors are not as good as there is a risk of stabbing while cutting something else. You can also add a solid stick like a marlinspike to your kit to help